=== Worked example: D(8)-triple (a,b,c) = (1,8,17) ===
Verify D(n)-triple property:
  ab + n = 16 = 4^2
  ac + n = 25 = 5^2
  bc + n = 144 = 12^2

Defining polynomial f(x) = 136*x^3 + 1288*x^2 + 1664*x + 512
Weierstrass model E     = Elliptic Curve defined by y^2 = x^3 + 1288*x^2 + 
226304*x + 9469952 over Rational Field
a-invariants            = [ 0, 1288, 0, 226304, 9469952 ]
Discriminant            = 78824057314738176
j-invariant             = 3590714269297/73410624

Rational 2-torsion E(Q)[2] = Abelian Group isomorphic to Z/2 + Z/2
Defined on 2 generators
Relations:
2*T2.1 = 0
2*T2.2 = 0
Explicit 2-torsion points (on the integral model) :
  P_a = (-bc*n,  0) = (-1088, 0)
  P_b = (-ac*n,  0) = (-136, 0)
  P_c = (-ab*n,  0) = (-64, 0)

